HEADWORD: Rissoid
<hw>Ris"soid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Rissoa</ets>, the typical genus ( fr. A. <ets>Risso</ets>, an
Italian naturalist) + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of very numerous species of small spiral gastropods of the
genus <gen>Rissoa</gen>, or family <fam>Rissoidae</fam>, found both in
fresh and salt water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

